1. LAUNCH EC2 INSTANCE UBUNTU 20.40 with security group (add port 8080)

2. CONNECT THROUGH SSH

3. EXECUTE THE FOLLOWING COMMANDS 

---> sudo apt-get update
---> sudo apt install openjdk-8-jdk
---> wget -q -O - https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io.key | sudo apt-key add -
---> sudo sh -c 'echo deb http://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list'
---> sudo apt update
---> sudo apt install jenkins
---> sudo systemctl status jenkins

Got to EC2 instance

4. COPY PUBLIC IP ADDRESS OF THAT IENKINS INSTANCE AND OPEN WITH :8080 PORT
     ______jenkins unlock site opens (copy that /var path) and go to terminal
     
5. sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
_______(it generates password copy that and paste in that jenkins unlock site)

6. CLICK INSTALL SUGGESTED PLUGINS

7. CREAT ADMIN USER  {USERNAME, PASSWORD, FULL NAME EMAIL ADDRESS}


[----------JENKINS IS READY!----------]
